 a lady who stayed here at the same time as Mr Knight, that is in June 1929?'

'What lady?' he asked in the elenctic tones of Lewis Carroll's caterpillar.

'I'm not sure of her name,' I said nervously.

'Then how do you expect me to find her?' he said with a shrug.

'She was Russian,' I said. 'Perhaps you remember a Russian lady — a young

lady — and well... good looking?'

'Nous avons eu beaucoup de jolies dames,'

he replied getting more and more distant. 'How should I remember?'

